Frances made to his development as an artist. Robert and Frances Flaherty charts her transformation from a Bryn Mawr bluestocking to the partner of a frontier explorer and offers her unique perspective as his collaborator and publicist.From iron prospector to photographer to filmmaker, Flaherty's early life is situated in the context of his explorations of the Canadian north and its peoples, the development of modern cinema, the rise of modernism, and his association with significant figures such as Alfred Adler, Franz Boas, Edward Curtis, and Alfred Steiglitz.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aInuit in motion pictures. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszUnited StatesvDiaries. 7aHISTORY / Reference.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780773572775?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773572775423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773572775/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles